      "writtenOn": "2020-11-23T23:26:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For Android, there is a key layout file that determines that maps Linux key to Android key. Also, there is a key character mapping file that will determine the final symbol based on the modifier and key. https://www.google.com/search?q\u003dandroid+kcm\u0026oq\u003dandroid+kcm\u0026aqs\u003dchrome..69i57j0i22i30i457j0i22i30j69i60j69i64j69i60l3.1759j0j7\u0026sourceid\u003dchrome\u0026ie\u003dUTF-8\n\n\nThis file in frameworks/base will determine the final symbol and ctrl and meta key won\u0027t really affect the output. https://android.googlesource.com/platform/frameworks/base/+/refs/heads/master/data/keyboards/qwerty2.kcm\n\nSo even if we send meta and ctrl into android system, I don\u0027t think it will not really affect the behavior of Android. I prefer to not change this code at all for stability since it might affect Android.",
      "parentUuid": "0c780d4f_2856aa28",
